ades, Isaac Israeli will be essential reading for students and scholars of medieval philosophy and Jewish studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aJewish philosophy. 0aPhilosophy, Medieval. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aphilosophy, judaism, religion, spirituality, platonism, neo-platonism, middle ages, influence, becoming, creation, love, desire, sense perception, imagination, medieval, spirit and soul, substances, definitions, mantua text, elements, wisdom, intellect, nature, natural causality, emanation, prophecy, union, illumination, purification, nonfiction.1 aAltmann, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAltmann, Alexander.1 aIvry, Alfred L.1 aStern, S. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStern, S.M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStern, Samuel M.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226016153423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226016153/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles